  <body>
    <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="PeruTM1.6">
<l>aḷimalarmē layaṉaraṉin tiraṉō ṭēṉai</l>
<l>yamararkaḷtaṅ kuḻuvumaram paiyaru maṟṟum</l>
<l>teḷimaticēr muṉivarkaḷtaṅ kuḻuvu muntit</l>
<l>ticaiticaiyiṉ malartūvic ceṉṟu cērum</l>
<l>kaḷimalarcēr poḻilaraṅkat turaka mēṟik</l>
<l>kaṇvaḷaruṅ kaṭalvaṇṇar kamalak kaṇṇum</l>
<l>oḷimaticēr tirumukamuṅ kaṇṭu koṇṭeṉ</l>
<l>ṉuḷḷamika veṉṟukolō vuruku nāḷē.</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>When is the day that my heart shall greatly melt beholding</l>
<l>the lotus eyes and the radiant moon-like holy face of</l>
<l>the ocean-hued One, who sleeps having climbed upon the serpent</l>
<l rend="indent">in Raṅgam, which has groves with blossoms [dripping] with honey,</l>
<l rend="indent">[and which,] Aja - on a lotus [sought by] bees -, Hara,</l>
<l rend="indent">a group of other immortals along with Indra, and Rambhā and the like,</l>
<l rend="indent">and moreover, a group of ascetics with clear minds,</l>
<l rend="indent">go to and reach, jostling [against each other] and strewing blossoms in all directions?</l>
      </lg>
    </div>
  </body>
